  "text": "The myotubes were analysed for protein degradation using procedures from Gomes-Marcondes et al [CITATION_1] . Differentiated myotubes grown in six-well plates were labelled with L-[2,6 3 H] phenylalanine (0.67 µCi.mmol -1 in DMEM added with cold phenylalanine 2 mmol.L -1 ) in 2 mL DMEM containing 2% horse serum. After 24 h, the myotubes were washed three times in PBS, followed by the addition of fresh DMEM without phenol red, and then the cells were subsequently treated with WF (3, 5, 10, 15, 20 and 25 µg.mL -1 ) for 24, 48 and 72 h. The protein degradation was determined measuring the radioactivity of the cell supernatant released into the medium using a Beckmam LS 6000TA liquid scintillation counter, and expressed as CPM per µg of cellular protein.",
